    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> the live-documentation is the list of widgets, it's the main/simple documentation hosted on the website\n\nOk so the live documentation website that we are building in this repository will be the one available on algolia.com also. How will it integrate technically since it's a different codebase from the algolia.com website?\n\nI feel this should live in his own repo in the end, what do you think? I see no advantage right now of storing it along with the code. But that's what react is doing in the end :D https://github.com/facebook/react/tree/master/docs\n",
